Taskboard
Overview
This project is a Task Board, also known as a Kanban Board, built using HTML, Bootstrap, and jQuery. The application allows users to manage tasks by adding new tasks to the board and moving them through different stages of progress (To Do, In Progress, and Done). The layout is responsive and utilizes various external libraries for styling and interaction.

Features
Add Tasks: A modal form allows users to add new tasks with details such as title, due date, and description. Three Columns for Task Progression: To Do: For tasks that need to be started. In Progress: For tasks currently being worked on. Done: For completed tasks. Modal Form: Uses Bootstrap modal to input task details. Task Management: Tasks can be added dynamically to the board.

Technology Stack
HTML5: For structuring the layout of the application. CSS3: Used for styling the layout with custom styles and Bootstrap. JavaScript (jQuery): Used for DOM manipulation and handling task functionality. Bootstrap 5: A front-end CSS framework for responsive design and modal functionality. jQuery UI: For handling interactive elements such as date pickers. Day.js: A minimal JavaScript library for manipulating dates and times.

Libraries & CDN Links

Bootstrap 5: Provides layout and styling, including modals and responsive design. https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.1.3/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.min.js Font Awesome: Icons for use within buttons and other UI elements. https://use.fontawesome.com/releases/v5.8.1/css/all.css Google Fonts: For custom typography. https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Open+Sans&display=swap jQuery: For handling DOM manipulation and AJAX requests. https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.4.1.min.js jQuery UI: For interactive widgets like date picker. https://code.jquery.com/ui/1.13.1/jquery-ui.min.js Day.js: For managing date and time in a simple and fast way. https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/dayjs@1.11.3/dayjs.min.jsLicense

